This is a simple console-based To-Do List application implemented in C#. The application allows users to add tasks, view existing tasks, and exit the application. It uses a list to store tasks and provides a menu-driven interface for user interaction.

How to Use
Run the Application:

Compile and run the program using a C# compiler or an integrated development environment (IDE).
Menu Options:

The application will display a menu with the following options:
1. Add Task: Allows the user to add a new task to the to-do list.
2. View Tasks: Displays the existing tasks in the to-do list.
3. Exit: Exits the application.
Adding a Task:

Choose option 1, enter the task when prompted, and press Enter.
The application will confirm the successful addition of the task.
Viewing Tasks:

Choose option 2 to view the existing tasks in the to-do list.
If there are no tasks, it will notify the user. Otherwise, it will display the tasks with their corresponding numbers.
Exiting the Application:

Choose option 3 to exit the application.
A goodbye message will be displayed.
Invalid Choices:

If the user enters an invalid choice, the application will display an error message.
